    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - HOOD, GRILLE AND FENDERS - IC BUS - DESCRIPTION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>HOOD</title>
            <para>The hood is a fiberglass, one-piece type (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900501">Figure 1</hotlnk>). The narrowed tilt fiberglass hood provides aerodynamics,
                while still enclosing the air cleaner. The design facilitates improved lower frontal driver visibility
                as required by state and regional municipalities. The grille is a separate removable assembly painted
                the same color as the fiberglass hood.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0900501" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900501.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="232px" resolution="100"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. IC BUS Hood</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>The hood for the IC BUS is a tilting type hood, easily tilted for service access.</para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
